doQuery

protected java.util.List<Transfer> doQuery()
                                    throws DatabaseException
Fetches the BI Transfer header data from the database.

All BI transfer header header records associated with a status of “B”, “C”, “F”, and “R” are fetch from the database and packaged into a List collection of Transfer objects.

editHeader

protected void editHeader(Transfer item)
The handler for opening the BI Tranfer Header Edit Dialog for a given Tranfer record.

The incoming transfer object, item, is tagged or identified as a BI transfer type. This is done as a means of providing additional information to common transfer header edit process so that the appropriate resources are utilized for the item.

updateHeaderStatus

protected boolean updateHeaderStatus(java.lang.String newStatus)
Updates the status of the BI Transfer record to the value of newStatus.

Overrides:
updateHeaderStatus in class CommonTransferFrame
Parameters:
newStatus - the status that will be applied to the transfer record. Valid values are "F" (Finish) and "C" (Closed).
Returns:
true when the BI Transfer Header's status is updated successfully as Finish or Unfinish. Otherwise, false is returned and the update status is aborted.
